&nbsp;I'm considering making a rum carrot cake. &nbsp;All the recipes I find are for making it from scratch.&nbsp;I want to just use a mix, and add rum. So, should I replace some of the oil with the rum, or replace some of the water with rum, and how much should I use... and what kind of rum, I don't know much about it. Do I use the clear stuff or the yellow/gold stuff? &nbsp;
Also, if I use rum in the icing as well as the cake, would that be too much rum? Should I just stick to putting it in the cake?
Any advice?

&nbsp;The results of the presidential election restored my faith in my fellow Americans.&nbsp;
Too bad that victory was tainted by my fellow Californians ripping my rights away from me. &nbsp;My heart breaks thinking of all of my married brothers and sisters that are going to have their marriage made invalid. &nbsp;I'm actually ashamed to call myself a Californian today. &nbsp;
This cannot go unanswered. We cannot let ourselves be treated this way. I have no idea how to fix this situation, but I know we can't just shut up and accept it.


So what's next? How about next year we propose to make marriage just between a white man and a white woman. Or better yet, how about between only a white christian man and a white christian woman, that's what you &quot;yes&quot; people ultimately want isn't it?&nbsp;
Know this, all of you who voted yes on 8, this will come around and bite you in the ass. And when it does, I will have nothing to say to you except, &quot;you did it to yourself&quot;.
